@startuml
title USF Runtime Flow - Startup and Tick Contracts
left to right direction

rectangle "Typed USF Scripts\n(mod/modpack + metric family + scale + realizer + phenomenon/model)" as Scripts
rectangle "Bootstrap Composer\n(modpack selection + validation + registry materialization)" as Boot
rectangle "Runtime Registries\n(catalog + runtime concept view + typed registries)" as Reg

package "USF Tick Domains" {
  rectangle "Substrate Runtime" as Sub
  rectangle "Realization Runtime" as Real
  rectangle "Phenomenon Runtime" as Phen
  rectangle "Capability Commit Runtime" as Cap
}

rectangle "Canonical Runtime Authority\n(scale/chunk metric + phenomenon/model records)" as Canon
rectangle "Derived Runtime Caches\n(summary/decision/artifact state)" as Derived
rectangle "Bevy ECS Runtime" as ECS

Scripts -[#1E88E5]-> Boot : register typed definitions in startup bootstrap
Boot -[#43A047]-> Reg : materialize deterministic registries in startup bootstrap
Reg -[#43A047]-> Sub : drives runtime domain inputs in deterministic phase order

Sub -[#FB8C00]-> Real : emits substrate summaries and signals in phase handoff
Real -[#FB8C00]-> Phen : emits realization decisions and support intents in phase handoff
Phen -[#FB8C00]-> Cap : emits typed capability intents and canonical update intents in phase handoff

Cap -[#43A047]-> ECS : commits capability effects via channel backends
Sub -[#43A047]-> Derived : updates substrate summaries in runtime cache layer
Real -[#43A047]-> Derived : updates decision streams in runtime cache layer
Phen -[#43A047]-> Canon : reconciles phenomenon/model authority in canonical layer
Cap -[#43A047]-> Canon : reconciles accepted canonical mutations in canonical layer
Derived -[#8E24AA]-> Sub : feeds next-tick rebuild inputs via bounded derivation chain

note right of Cap
Evaluator hooks are optional and contract-declared.
Failures are panic-fast.
end note

note bottom
Definition surfaces are sealed after startup bootstrap.
Runtime definition mutation requires explicit full rebootstrap.
end note
@enduml
